# Refining UI Animation & Layouts

## Goal Description
The user wants to refine the layout of [FilesPage](file:///c:/Users/Sami/client-dashboard/pages/FilesPage.tsx#147-764) and [ProjectFilesPage](file:///c:/Users/Sami/client-dashboard/pages/ProjectFilesPage.tsx#125-739). We will:
1. Improve the animations of the filter and upload panels to be smooth using `framer-motion` spring animations (`awwwards-animations` workflow).
2. Fix the layout issue where expanding the filter panel obscures or breaks the layout for the upload button.
3. Make the filter and upload panels mutually exclusive (only one can be open at a time).
4. Remove the title elements and shift the action row (Filters, Upload) up to reclaim screen estate.
5. Ensure the active extended panel (Upload or Filter) spans the full width of its container.

## Proposed Changes

### [components/files/FilterPanel.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Sami/client-dashboard/components/files/FilterPanel.tsx)
- **[MODIFY]** Extract the "Filter" button out of the component, or allow the component to receive `isOpen` and `onToggle` props. 
- *Better Architecture:* Split the component so the parent can render the Toolbar buttons together in a `flex-row`, and conditionally render the expanding `FilterPanelBody` in a full-width container directly underneath. I will remove the internal `useState(true)` and turn it into a purely controlled, render-only panel body.

### [pages/FilesPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Sami/client-dashboard/pages/FilesPage.tsx)
- **[MODIFY]** Remove the `<h1>Files</h1>` heading.
- **[MODIFY]** Move the Filter and Upload buttons to the same line as the ViewMode selector and Refresh toggles.
- **[MODIFY]** Introduce mutually exclusive states: `openPanel: 'filters' | 'upload' | null`.
- **[MODIFY]** Render a single, full-width `AnimatePresence` wrapper below the header row that houses either the Upload UI or the Filter panel. This will use the requested `framer-motion` configurations.

### [pages/ProjectFilesPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Sami/client-dashboard/pages/ProjectFilesPage.tsx)
- **[MODIFY]** Replicate the same changes here. Remove the project files heading.
- **[MODIFY]** Add mutually exclusive `openPanel` state.
- **[MODIFY]** Consolidate header actions into a single row.
- **[MODIFY]** Place the full-width animated container directly below the row.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run lint` and `npm run test` (if applicable) to ensure no syntax errors were introduced.

### Manual Verification
1. Navigate to `/` (FilesPage).
2. Verify the page header title is removed and buttons are moved up.
3. Click "Filters". Ensure it slides down smoothly.
4. Click "Upload". Ensure the Filters slide up, and Upload slides down smoothly (mutually exclusive).
5. Open Project Files via sidebar, and run through the same steps (3, 4) to verify consistency.
